      <scopecontent>
         <p>Samuel
Minot's letters to his brother John chiefly describe his studies at Phillips Academy in Andover,
Massachusetts. He also discusses travels in New England, and his political support of the Whig
Party and of the abolition of slavery in New Hampshire.</p>
      </scopecontent>
